val path="/data/archive/"
val names=List("olist_customers_dataset.csv","olist_orders_dataset.csv","olist_order_payments_dataset.csv")
val schema_cs=new StructType()
.add("customer_id",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("customer_unique_id",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("customer_zip_code",IntegerType,nullable=true)
.add("customer_city",StringType,nullable=true)
.add("customer_state",StringType,nullable=true)

val customer_data=spark.read.schema(schema_cs).option("sep",",").option("header","true").csv(path+names(0))


val schema_od=new StructType()
.add("order_id",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("customer_id",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("order_status",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("order_purchase_time",TimestampType,nullable=false)
.add("order_approved_at",TimestampType)
.add("order_delivered_arrier_at",TimestampType)
.add("order_delivered_customer_date",TimestampType)
.add("order_estimated_delivery_date",TimestampType)

val order_data=spark.read.schema(schema_od).option("sep",",").option("header","true").csv(path+names(1))


val schema_pd=new StructType()
.add("order_id",StringType,nullable=false)
.add("payment_sequential",IntegerType)
.add("payment_type",StringType)
.add("payment_installments",IntegerType)

val query="""
  with customer_info as(
 select distinct customer_id as customer_id,
       row_number() over(order by customer_id) as rows
       from customer_data)
     ,customer_modify as(
     select customer_id,
           case when rows<10 then concat('u_0',cast(rows as string)) 
           else concat('u-',cast(rows as string)) end as user_id
           from customer_info)
    ,order_modify as(
    select user_id,
           concat(user_id,"-",substring(o.order_id,1,4)) as unique_order_id,
           substring(order_purchase_time,1,10) as stamp,
           order_status as order_status,
           pd.payment_type as payment_type,
           pd.payment_value as payment_value
           from order_data as o 
           left join customer_modify as c 
           on o.customer_id=c.customer_id
           left join product_data as pd
           on o.order_id=pd.order_id )
           select * from order_modify
 """

 
spark.sql(query).createOrReplaceTempView("customer_transactions")

## Analysis 


### Part 1) Daily Transactions 

The sales revenue had increased steadily until the end of the year,2017, with relatively small sudden increases taking place from time to time.  The company experienced a dramatic increase in sales revenue all-time for a short period.  There must have been a one-time event available for customers. Right after it recorded the best performance, the sales had plummeted to the previous range for a while.  But after one month, this event may have attracted more customers to boost their sales.Based on December of the year 2017, we divided the whole into two phases. The average figures in the first phase moved between 10,000 and 20,000 while those in the second phase between 20,000 and 50,000.



###### Here are few points we should take a further investigation on

1) Find out exactly what caused the sales to rise at an unprecedented level

2) Round every five-month, the sales drop at sudden and recovered slowly. Is there any possible measure to cope with the decline in sales readily?

%spark.sql
select stamp, 
      coalesce(sum(payment_value),0) as purchase_amount,
      avg(sum(payment_value)) over(order by stamp rows between 6 preceding and current row) as seven_day_avg,
      case when  7=count(*) over(order by stamp rows between 6 preceding and current row) then avg(sum(payment_value)) over(order by stamp rows between 6 preceding and current row) end as strict_seven_avg
      from customer_transactions
      group by stamp
      order by stamp

SELECT stamp,
       substring(stamp,1,7) as year_month,
       sum(payment_value) as total_amount,
       sum(sum(payment_value)) over(partition by substring(stamp,1,7) order by stamp rows between unbounded preceding and current row) as agg_amount 
FROM customer_transactions
GROUP BY stamp
ORDER BY stamp
